library(ggplot2)
SRX = function (time, y, parms) { 
  
S <- y[1]
R <- y[2]
X <- y[3]
N <- S + R + X

m <- parms["m"]
c <- parms["c"]
beta <- parms["beta"]
gamma <- parms["gamma"]
mu <- parms["mu"]
tau1 <- parms["tau1"]
tau2 <- parms["tau2"]

dS <- m * mu + beta * S * X - (tau1 + tau2 + gamma + mu) * S
dR <- beta * (1 - c) * R * X - (mu + tau2 + gamma) * R
dX <- (1 - m)*mu + (tau1 + tau2 + gamma)*S + (tau2 + gamma)*R - beta*S*X - beta*(1 - c)*R*X - mu*X

return(list(c(dS, dR, dX)))
}
init <- c(S = 0.0001, R = 0.0001, X = 0.9998)
times <- seq(0, 250, by = 1)
params <- c(beta = 1, c = 0.05, mu = 1/10, gamma = 1/30, m = 0.75, tau1 = 1/5, tau2 = 1/10)
data_out <- ode(y = init, times = times, func = SRX, parms = params) 

out <- data.frame(data_out)

ggplot(out, aes(x = time)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = S, color = "S")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = R, color = "R")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = X, color = "X")) +
  labs(x = "Time", y = "Frequency", color = "Variable") +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("S" = "green", "R" = "red", "X" = "blue"),
                     labels = c("S" = "S", "R" = "R", "X" = "X"))

beta_range <- seq(0, 3, by = 0.2)
tau1_range <- seq(0, 0.5, by = 0.05)
tau2_range <- seq(0, 0.5, by = 0.05)

results_beta <- data.frame()
results_tau1 <- data.frame()
results_tau2 <- data.frame()

for (beta in beta_range) {
  parameters <- c(beta=beta, c=0.05, mu=1/10, gamma=1/30, m=0.75, tau1 = 1/5, tau2 = 1/10)
  out <- ode(y = init, times = times, func = SRX, parms = parameters)
  results_beta <- rbind(results_beta, slice_tail(as.data.frame(out), n = 1))
}

for (tau1 in tau1_range) {
  parameters <- c(beta=1, c=0.05, mu=1/10, gamma=1/30, m=0.75, tau1 = tau1, tau2 = 1/10)
  out <- ode(y = init, times = times, func = SRX, parms = parameters)
  results_tau1 <- rbind(results_tau1, slice_tail(as.data.frame(out), n = 1))
}

for (tau2 in tau2_range) {
  parameters <- c(beta=1, c=0.05, mu=1/10, gamma=1/30, m=0.75, tau1 = 1/5, tau2 = tau2)
  out <- ode(y = init, times = times, func = SRX, parms = parameters)
  results_tau2 <- rbind(results_tau2, slice_tail(as.data.frame(out), n = 1))
}

Beta is the transmission rate of the disease. With the increase in beta, only the resistant bacteria R increases, and the uninfected decrease.

Tau1 is the level of treatment with drug 1. With the increase of tau1, the prevalence of resistant bacteria increase and the prevalence of sensitive bacteria decreases.

Tau2 is the treatment with drug 2. With the increase of tau2, the prevalence of resistant bacteria to drug 1 reduces but the level of prevalence of sensitive bacteria increases.
